
@startuml

' Define the main classes and their attributes and relationships

class Employee {
  - name: String
  - socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class CreativeEmployee {
  + isOscarWinner: Boolean
}

class Director {
  - assistantName: String
  -- extends CreativeEmployee
}

class Actor {
  - education: String
  -- extends CreativeEmployee
}

class Technician {
  - fieldOfActivity: String
}

' Inheritance hierarchy for CreativeEmployee
CreativeEmployee <|-- Director
CreativeEmployee <|-- Actor

class FilmSet {
  - location: String
  - films: List<Film>
}

class Film {
  - title: String
  - yearOfRelease: Integer
  - genre: String
  - filmSets: List<FilmSet>
  - screenplay: Screenplay
}

class Screenwriter {
  - name: String
  - mostSuccessfulFilm: String
  - screenplays: List<Screenplay>
}

class Screenplay {
  - title: String
  - version: String
  - date: Date
  - numberOfScenes: Integer
  - plot: String
  - basis: String (novel or concept)
  - film: Film
}

class Novel {
  - title: String
  - author: String
}

' Relationships

' Employees are part of a film set
FilmSet "1" -- "many" Employee : has

' Films are associated with multiple film sets
Film "1" -- "many" FilmSet : is shot at

' A film has one screenplay
Film "1" -- "1" Screenplay : is based on

' A screenplay is written by one screenwriter
Screenplay "1" -- "1" Screenwriter : is written by

' A screenplay may be based on a novel
Screenplay "1" -- "0..1" Novel : is based on

' Actors are part of a film
Film "1" -- "many" Actor : includes

@enduml

### Explanation:
- **Employee** is the base class for all employees.
- **Director** and **Actor** inherit from **CreativeEmployee**, which also includes Oscar status.
- **Technician** is a separate type of employee with activity field.
- **FilmSet** contains multiple **Films** and has a location.
- **Film** has a title, release year, genre, and is linked to a **Screenplay**.
- **Screenplay** is written by a **Screenwriter**, has metadata, and can be based on a **Novel**.
- **Actors** are part of a **Film**.

